A man accused of masterminding the theft of a $5million Stradivarius violin pleaded guilty to robbery robbery Friday.

The plea deal for Salah Salahadyn comes nearly eight months after the 300-year-old instrument was snatched from a musician who was attacked with a stun gun following a performance in Milwaukee, Wisconsin.

Salahadyn, 41, was taken into custody after changing his plea during a hearing in Milwaukee County Circuit Court. He could face up to 10 years in prison when sentenced November 10.

