The other man charged in the violin case, Universal Knowledge Allah, 36, was sentenced to three-and-a-half years in prison after pleading guilty in May to being party to felony robbery, the same charge to which Salahadyn pleaded guilty. 

Prosecutors said Allah provided the stun gun used to attack Frank Almond.

